<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 5:22PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Davie and
northwestern Rowan Counties through 600 PM EDT...
At 522 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Mocksville, or near Cooleemee, moving east at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Mocksville, Salisbury, Spencer, Cooleemee, Fork Church and Woodleaf.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
